        <title>Full Spectrum (350-500 nm) Leaf and Canopy Spectral Reflectance, Seward Peninsula, Alaska, 2017</title>
      </citeinfo>
    </citation>
    <descript>
      <abstract>Measurements of leaf-level and vegetation canopy spectral reflectance.  Leaf-level measurements were made with a full-spectrum (i.e. 350-2500 nm) spectroradiometer using a 1.2 meter fiber optic cable and a leaf-clip foreoptic.  Canopy reflectance was also measured using a full-spectrum instrument and either a 4deg or 8deg field-of-view (FOV) lens over the vegetation canopy.  The measurement height above the canopy is recorded in the measurement metadata.</abstract>
    </descript>
